/* A standard type pattern match:
  case ErrorType =>
    // internal: error
  case WildcardType =>
    // internal: unknown
  case NoType =>
  case NoPrefix =>
  case ThisType(sym) =>
    // sym.this.type
  case SingleType(pre, sym) =>
    // pre.sym.type
  case ConstantType(value) =>
    // int(2)
  case TypeRef(pre, sym, args) => 
    // pre.sym[targs]
  case RefinedType(parents, defs) =>
    // parent1 with ... with parentn { defs }
  case AnnotatedType(attribs, tp, selfsym) =>
    // tp @attribs

  // the following are non-value types; you cannot write them down in Scala source.

  case TypeBounds(lo, hi) =>  
    // >: lo <: hi
  case ClassInfoType(parents, defs, clazz) =>
    // same as RefinedType except as body of class
  case MethodType(paramtypes, result) =>
    // (paramtypes)result
  case PolyType(tparams, result) =>
    // [tparams]result where result is a MethodType or ClassInfoType
    // or
    // []T  for a eval-by-name type
  case ExistentialType(tparams, result) =>
    // exists[tparams]result

  // the last five types are not used after phase `typer'. 

  case OverloadedType(pre, tparams, alts) =>
    // all alternatives of an overloaded ident
  case AntiPolyType(pre: Type, targs) =>
  case TypeVar(_, _) =>
    // a type variable
  case DeBruijnIndex(level, index)
*/

trait trait Types extends java.lang.Object with ScalaObjectTypes { 
  self: SymbolTable =>

  /** A proxy for a type (identified by field `underlying') that forwards most 
   *  operations to it (for exceptions, see WrappingProxy, which forwards even more operations).
   *  every operation that is overridden for some kind of types should be forwarded.
   */
  trait trait SimpleTypeProxy extends Types.this.Type with ScalaObjectSimpleTypeProxy extends Types.this.TypeType {
    def => Types.this.Typeunderlying: Types.this.TypeType

    // the following operations + those in RewrappingTypeProxy are all operations 
    // in class Type that are overridden in some subclass
    // Important to keep this up-to-date when new operations are added!
    override def => BooleanisTrivial = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> BooleanisTrivial
    override def => BooleanisHigherKinded: BooleanBoolean = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> BooleanisHigherKinded
    override def => BooleanisNotNull = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> BooleanisNotNull
    override def => BooleanisError = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> BooleanisError
    override def => BooleanisErroneous = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> BooleanisErroneous
    override def => BooleanisStable: BooleanBoolean = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> BooleanisStable
    override def => BooleanisVolatile = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> BooleanisVolatile
    override def => Types.this.TypefinalResultType = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.TypefinalResultType
    override def => IntparamSectionCount = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> IntparamSectionCount
    override def => List[Types.this.Type]paramTypes = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> List[Types.this.Type]paramTypes
    override def => Types.this.SymboltermSymbol = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.SymboltermSymbol
    override def => Types.this.SymboltermSymbolDirect = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.SymboltermSymbolDirect
    override def => List[Types.this.Symbol]typeParams = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> List[Types.this.Symbol]typeParams
    override def => List[Types.this.Symbol]boundSyms = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> List[Types.this.Symbol]boundSyms
    override def => Types.this.SymboltypeSymbol = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.SymboltypeSymbol
    override def => Types.this.SymboltypeSymbolDirect = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.SymboltypeSymbolDirect
    override def => Types.this.Typewiden = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.Typewiden
    override def => Types.this.TypetypeOfThis = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.TypetypeOfThis
    override def => Types.this.TypeBoundsbounds = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.TypeBoundsbounds
    override def => List[Types.this.Type]parents = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> List[Types.this.Type]parents
    override def => Types.this.Typeprefix = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.Typeprefix
    override def => Types.this.Scopedecls = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.Scopedecls
    override def (Types.this.Symbol)Types.this.TypebaseType(Types.this.Symbolclazz: Types.this.SymbolSymbol) = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.(Types.this.Symbol)Types.this.TypebaseType(Types.this.Symbolclazz)
    override def => Types.this.BaseTypeSeqbaseTypeSeq = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.BaseTypeSeqbaseTypeSeq
    override def => IntbaseTypeSeqDepth = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> IntbaseTypeSeqDepth
    override def => List[Types.this.Symbol]baseClasses = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> List[Types.this.Symbol]baseClasses
  }

  /** A proxy for a type (identified by field `underlying') that forwards most 
   *  operations to it. Every operation that is overridden for some kind of types is
   *  forwarded here. Some opererations are rewrapped again.
   */
  trait trait RewrappingTypeProxy extends Types.this.Type with Types.this.SimpleTypeProxy with ScalaObjectRewrappingTypeProxy extends Types.this.SimpleTypeProxySimpleTypeProxy {
    protected def (Types.this.Type)Types.this.TypemaybeRewrap(Types.this.Typenewtp: Types.this.TypeType) = Types.this.Typeif (Types.this.Typenewtp (AnyRef)Booleaneq => Types.this.Typeunderlying) Types.this.RewrappingTypeProxythis else (Types.this.Type)Types.this.Typerewrap(Types.this.Typenewtp)
    protected def (Types.this.Type)Types.this.Typerewrap(Types.this.Typenewtp: Types.this.TypeType): Types.this.TypeType

    // the following are all operations in class Type that are overridden in some subclass
    // Important to keep this up-to-date when new operations are added!
    override def => Types.this.Typewiden = (Types.this.Type)Types.this.TypemaybeRewrap(=> Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.Typewiden)
    override def => Types.this.Typenarrow = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.Typenarrow
    override def => Types.this.Typedeconst = (Types.this.Type)Types.this.TypemaybeRewrap(=> Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.Typedeconst)
    override def => Types.this.TyperesultType = (Types.this.Type)Types.this.TypemaybeRewrap(=> Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.TyperesultType)
    override def (List[Types.this.Type])Types.this.TyperesultType(List[Types.this.Type]actuals: List[Types.this.Type]List[Type]) = (Types.this.Type)Types.this.TypemaybeRewrap(=> Types.this.Typeunderlying.(List[Types.this.Type])Types.this.TyperesultType(List[Types.this.Type]actuals))
    override def => Types.this.TypefinalResultType = (Types.this.Type)Types.this.TypemaybeRewrap(=> Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.TypefinalResultType)
    override def => IntparamSectionCount = Int(0)0
    override def => List[Types.this.Type]paramTypes: List[Types.this.Type]List[Type] = object NilList()
    override def => List[Types.this.Type]typeArgs = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> List[Types.this.Type]typeArgs
    override def => Types.this.TypenotNull = (Types.this.Type)Types.this.TypemaybeRewrap(=> Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.TypenotNull)
    override def (List[Types.this.Symbol],List[Types.this.Type])Types.this.TypeinstantiateTypeParams(List[Types.this.Symbol]formals: List[Types.this.Symbol]List[Symbol], List[Types.this.Type]actuals: List[Types.this.Type]List[Type]) = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.(List[Types.this.Symbol],List[Types.this.Type])Types.this.TypeinstantiateTypeParams(List[Types.this.Symbol]formals, List[Types.this.Type]actuals)
    override def (Types.this.Symbol,AnyRef)Types.this.TypeskolemizeExistential(Types.this.Symbolowner: Types.this.SymbolSymbol, AnyReforigin: AnyRefAnyRef) = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.(Types.this.Symbol,AnyRef)Types.this.TypeskolemizeExistential(Types.this.Symbolowner, AnyReforigin)
    override def => Types.this.Typenormalize = (Types.this.Type)Types.this.TypemaybeRewrap(=> Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.Typenormalize)
    override def (Types.this.Symbol)Types.this.TypecloneInfo(Types.this.Symbolowner: Types.this.SymbolSymbol) = (Types.this.Type)Types.this.TypemaybeRewrap(=> Types.this.Typeunderlying.(Types.this.Symbol)Types.this.TypecloneInfo(Types.this.Symbolowner))
    override def => java.lang.StringprefixString = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> java.lang.StringprefixString
    override def => BooleanisComplete = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> BooleanisComplete
    override def (Types.this.Symbol)Unitcomplete(Types.this.Symbolsym: Types.this.SymbolSymbol) = => Types.this.Typeunderlying.(Types.this.Symbol)Unitcomplete(Types.this.Symbolsym)
    override def (Types.this.Symbol)Unitload(Types.this.Symbolsym: Types.this.SymbolSymbol) { => Types.this.Typeunderlying.(Types.this.Symbol)Unitload(Types.this.Symbolsym) }
    override def (List[Types.this.AnnotationInfo])Types.this.TypewithAttributes(List[Types.this.AnnotationInfo]attribs: List[Types.this.AnnotationInfo]List[AnnotationInfo]) = (Types.this.Type)Types.this.TypemaybeRewrap(=> Types.this.Typeunderlying.(List[Types.this.AnnotationInfo])Types.this.TypewithAttributes(List[Types.this.AnnotationInfo]attribs))
    override def => Types.this.TypewithoutAttributes = (Types.this.Type)Types.this.TypemaybeRewrap(=> Types.this.Typeunderlying.=> Types.this.TypewithoutAttributes)
  }

  /** The base class for all types */
  abstract class class Type extends java.lang.Object with ScalaObjectType {
    
    /** Types for which asSeenFrom always is the identity, no matter what
     *  prefix or owner.
     */
    def => BooleanisTrivial: BooleanBoolean = Boolean(false)false

    /** Is this type higher-kinded, i.e., is it a type constructor @M */
    def => BooleanisHigherKinded: BooleanBoolean = Boolean(false)false 
    
    /** Does this type denote a stable reference (i.e. singleton type)? */
    def => BooleanisStable: BooleanBoolean = Boolean(false)false

    /** Is this type dangerous (i.e. it might contain conflicting
     *  type information when empty, so that it can be constructed
     *  so that type unsoundness results.) A dangerous type has an underlying
     *  type of the form T_1 with T_n { decls }, where one of the
     *  T_i (i > 1) is an abstract type.
     */
    def => BooleanisVolatile: BooleanBoolean = Boolean(false)false

    /** Is this type guaranteed not to have `null' as a value? */
    def => BooleanisNotNull: BooleanBoolean = Boolean(false)false

    /** Does this depend on an enclosing method parameter? */
    def => BooleanisDependent: BooleanBoolean = object Types.this.IsDependentCollectorIsDependentCollector.(Types.this.Type)Booleancollect(Types.this.Typethis)
 
    /** The term symbol associated with the type
      * Note that the symbol of the normalized type is returned (@see normalize)
      */
    def => Types.this.SymboltermSymbol: Types.this.SymbolSymbol = object Types.this.NoSymbolNoSymbol

    /** The type symbol associated with the type
      * Note that the symbol of the normalized type is returned (@see normalize)
      */
    def => Types.this.SymboltypeSymbol: Types.this.SymbolSymbol = object Types.this.NoSymbolNoSymbol

    /** The term symbol *directly* associated with the type
      */
    def => Types.this.SymboltermSymbolDirect: Types.this.SymbolSymbol = => Types.this.SymboltermSymbol

    /** The type symbol *directly* associated with the type
      */
    def => Types.this.SymboltypeSymbolDirect: Types.this.SymbolSymbol = => Types.this.SymboltypeSymbol

    /** The base type underlying a type proxy,
     *  identity on all other types */
    def => Types.this.Typeunderlying: Types.this.TypeType = Types.this.Typethis

    /** Widen from singleton type to its underlying non-singleton base type
     *  by applying one or more `underlying' derefernces,
     *  identity for all other types */
    def => Types.this.Typewiden: Types.this.TypeType = Types.this.Typethis

    /** Map a constant type or not-null-type to its underlying base type,
     *  identity for all other types */
    def => Types.this.Typedeconst: Types.this.TypeType = Types.this.Typethis

    /** The type of `this' of a class type or reference type
     */
    def => Types.this.TypetypeOfThis: Types.this.TypeType = => Types.this.SymboltypeSymbol.=> Types.this.TypetypeOfThis

    /** Map to a singleton type which is a subtype of this type.
     */
    def => Types.this.Typenarrow: Types.this.TypeType =
      Types.this.Typeif (=> scala.tools.nsc.Phasephase.=> BooleanerasedTypes) Types.this.Typethis
      else {
        val Types.this.Symbolcowner = (Types.this.Type)Types.this.SymbolcommonOwner(Types.this.Typethis)
        (List[Types.this.Type],Types.this.Symbol,Types.this.Scope,scala.tools.nsc.util.Position)Types.this.TyperefinedType((Types.this.Type*)List[Types.this.Type]List(Types.this.Typethis), Types.this.Symbolcowner, object Types.this.EmptyScopeEmptyScope, Types.this.Symbolcowner.=> scala.tools.nsc.util.Positionpos).=> Types.this.Typenarrow
      }

    /** For a TypeBounds type, itself;
     *  for a reference denoting an abstract type, its bounds,
     *  for all other types, a TypeBounds type all of whose bounds are this type.
     */
    def => Types.this.TypeBoundsbounds: Types.this.TypeBoundsTypeBounds = (Types.this.Type,Types.this.Type)Types.this.TypeBoundsmkTypeBounds(Types.this.Typethis, Types.this.Typethis)

    /** For a class or intersection type, its parents.
     *  For a TypeBounds type, the parents of its hi bound.
     *  inherited by typerefs, singleton types, and refinement types,
     *  The empty list for all other types */
    def => List[Types.this.Type]parents: List[Types.this.Type]List[Type] = object NilList()

    /** For a typeref or single-type, the prefix of the normalized type (@see normalize). NoType for all other types. */
    def => Types.this.Typeprefix: Types.this.TypeType = object Types.this.NoTypeNoType

    /** A chain of all typeref or singletype prefixes of this type, longest first */
    def => List[Types.this.Type]prefixChain: List[Types.this.Type]List[Type] = Types.this.Typethis List[Types.this.Type]match {
      List[Types.this.Type]case TypeRef(Types.this.Typepre, _, _) => Types.this.Typepre (Types.this.Type)List[Types.this.Type]:: Types.this.Typepre.=> List[Types.this.Type]prefixChain
      List[Types.this.Type]case SingleType(Types.this.Typepre, _) => Types.this.Typepre (Types.this.Type)List[Types.this.Type]:: Types.this.Typepre.=> List[Types.this.Type]prefixChain
      List[Nothing]case _ => object NilList()
    }

    /** For a typeref, its arguments. The empty list for all other types */
    def => List[Types.this.Type]typeArgs: List[Types.this.Type]List[Type] = object NilList()

    /** For a method or poly type, its direct result type, 
     *  the type itself for all other types */
    def => Types.this.TyperesultType: Types.this.TypeType = Types.this.Typethis

    def (List[Types.this.Type])Types.this.TyperesultType(List[Types.this.Type]actuals: List[Types.this.Type]List[Type]) = Types.this.Typethis

    def => Types.this.TyperesultApprox: Types.this.TypeType = (Types.this.Type)Types.this.TypeApproximateDeBruijnMap(=> Types.this.TyperesultType)

    /** For a curried method or poly type its non-method result type, 
     *  the type itself for all other types */
    def => Types.this.TypefinalResultType: Types.this.TypeType = Types.this.Typethis

    /** For a method or poly type, the number of its value parameter sections,
     *  0 for all other types */
    def => IntparamSectionCount: IntInt = Int(0)0

    /** For a method or poly type, the types of its first value parameter section,
     *  the empty list for all other types */
    def => List[Types.this.Type]paramTypes: List[Types.this.Type]List[Type] = object NilList()

    /** For a (potentially wrapped) poly type, its type parameters,
     *  the empty list for all other types */
    def => List[Types.this.Symbol]typeParams: List[Types.this.Symbol]List[Symbol] = object NilList()
  
    /** For a (potentially wrapped) poly or existential type, its bound symbols,

    def => List[Types.this.Symbol]boundSyms: List[Types.this.Symbol]List[Symbol] = object NilList()

    /** Mixin a NotNull trait unless type already has one */
    def => Types.this.TypenotNull: Types.this.TypeType = 
      Types.this.Typeif (=> BooleanisNotNull (Boolean)Boolean|| => scala.tools.nsc.Phasephase.=> BooleanerasedTypes) Types.this.Typethis else (Types.this.Type)Types.this.NotNullTypeNotNullType(Types.this.Typethis)
    
    /** Replace formal type parameter symbols with actual type arguments.

     * Amounts to substitution except for higher-kinded types. (See overridden method in TypeRef) -- @M (contact adriaan.moors at cs.kuleuven.be)
     */
    def (List[Types.this.Symbol],List[Types.this.Type])Types.this.TypeinstantiateTypeParams(List[Types.this.Symbol]formals: List[Types.this.Symbol]List[Symbol], List[Types.this.Type]actuals: List[Types.this.Type]List[Type]): Types.this.TypeType = Type.this.typethis.(List[Types.this.Symbol],List[Types.this.Type])Types.this.Typesubst(List[Types.this.Symbol]formals, List[Types.this.Type]actuals)

    def (Types.this.Symbol,AnyRef)Types.this.TypeskolemizeExistential(Types.this.Symbolowner: Types.this.SymbolSymbol, AnyReforigin: AnyRefAnyRef): Types.this.TypeType = Types.this.Typethis
    
    /** Reduce to beta eta-long normal form. Expands type aliases and converts higher-kinded TypeRef's to PolyTypes. @M */
    def => Types.this.Typenormalize = Types.this.Typethis // @MAT
    
    /** Is this type produced as a repair for an error? */
    def => BooleanisError: BooleanBoolean = => Types.this.SymboltypeSymbol.=> BooleanisError (Boolean)Boolean|| => Types.this.SymboltermSymbol.=> BooleanisError

    /** Is this type produced as a repair for an error? */
    def => BooleanisErroneous: BooleanBoolean = object Types.this.ErroneousCollectorErroneousCollector.(Types.this.Type)Booleancollect(Types.this.Typethis)

    /** Does this type denote a reference type which can be null? */
    // def isNullable: Boolean = false

    /** For a classtype or refined type, its defined or declared members;
     *  inherited by subtypes and typerefs.
     *  The empty scope for all other types */
    def => Types.this.Scopedecls: Types.this.ScopeScope = object Types.this.EmptyScopeEmptyScope

    /** The defined or declared members with name `name' in this type;
     *  an OverloadedSymbol if several exist, NoSymbol if none exist.
     *  Alternatives of overloaded symbol appear in the order they are declared.
     */
    def (Types.this.Name)Types.this.Symboldecl(Types.this.Namename: Types.this.NameName): Types.this.SymbolSymbol = (Types.this.Name,Int)Types.this.SymbolfindDecl(Types.this.Namename, Int(0)0)

    /** The non-private defined or declared members with name `name' in this type;
     *  an OverloadedSymbol if several exist, NoSymbol if none exist.
     *  Alternatives of overloaded symbol appear in the order they are declared.
     */
    def (Types.this.Name)Types.this.SymbolnonPrivateDecl(Types.this.Namename: Types.this.NameName): Types.this.SymbolSymbol = (Types.this.Name,Int)Types.this.SymbolfindDecl(Types.this.Namename, Int(4)PRIVATE)

    /** A list of all members of this type (defined or inherited)
     *  Members appear in linearization order of their owners.
     *  Members with the same owner appear in reverse order of their declarations.
     */

    /** The shortest sorted upwards closed array of types that contains

  /** A class representing intersection types with refinements of the form

    /** A refined type P1 with ... with Pn { decls } is volatile if

/* @MAT
whenever you see `tp.typeSymbol.isXXXX' and then act on tp based on that predicate, you're on thin ice, 
as `typeSymbol' (and `prefix') automatically normalize, but the other inspectors don't. 
In other words, even if `tp.normalize.sym.isXXX' is true, `tp.sym.isXXX' may be false (if sym were a public method to access the non-normalized typeSymbol)...

In retrospect, I think `tp.typeSymbol.isXXX' or (worse) `tp.typeSymbol==XXX' should be replaced by `val tp = tp0.asXXX'.  
A type's typeSymbol should never be inspected directly.
*/

  /** A class representing a polymorphic type or, if tparams.length == 0,

   *   Ideally, there would be a NullaryMethodType, but since the only polymorphic values are methods, it's not that problematic.
   *   More pressingly, we should add a TypeFunction type for anonymous type constructors -- for now, PolyType is used in:
   *     - normalize: for eta-expansion of type aliases
   *     - abstractTypeSig )

  /** A creator for existential types. This generates:
   *  
   *  tpe1 where { tparams }
   *
   *  where `tpe1' is the result of extrapolating `tpe' wrt to `tparams'. Extrapolating means
   *  that type variables in `tparams' occurring in covariant positions are replaced by upper bounds,
   *  (minus any SingletonClass markers),
   *  type variables in `tparams' occurring in contravariant positions are replaced by upper bounds,
   *  provided the resulting type is legal wrt to stability, and does not contain any
   *  type varianble in `tparams'.

   *  referenced by type `tpe1'.

  /** The raw to existential map converts a ``raw type'' to an existential type.
   *  It is necessary because we might have read a raw type of a 
   *  parameterized Java class from a class file. At the time we read the type
   *  the corresponding class file might still not be read, so we do not
   *  know what the type parameters of the type are. Therefore
   *  the conversion of raw types to existential types might not have taken place
   *  in ClassFileparser.sigToType (where it is usually done)
   */
  object object Types.this.rawToExistentialrawToExistential extends Types.this.TypeMapTypeMap {
    def (Types.this.Type)Types.this.Typeapply(Types.this.Typetp: Types.this.TypeType): Types.this.TypeType = Types.this.Typetp Types.this.Typematch {
      Types.this.Typecase TypeRef(Types.this.Typepre, Types.this.Symbolsym, (List[Types.this.Type])Some[List[Types.this.Type]]List()) if => Boolean!Types.this.Symbolsym.=> List[Types.this.Symbol]typeParams.=> BooleanisEmpty (Boolean)Boolean&& Types.this.Symbolsym.(Long)BooleanhasFlag(Long(1048576L)JAVA) =>

  /** A global counter for glb calls in the `specializes' query connected to the `addMembers'
   *  call in `glb'. There's a possible inifinite recursion when `specializes' calls
   *  memberType, which calls baseTypeSeq, which calls mergePrefixAndArgs, which calls glb.
   *  The counter breaks this recursion after two calls.
   *  If the recursion is broken, no member is added to the glb.
   */
